summary: Fic game.... Desperate to sleep, and hoping to dream of his scavenger, Kylo plopped onto his bed to discover Millicent curled up...
question: Fic game.... Desperate to sleep, and hoping to dream of his scavenger, Kylo plopped onto his bed to discover Millicent curled up on the pillow!
answer:
“Mrrrrowwwww,” the orange tabby purred at him imperiously, a tad too much like her owner for Kylo’s liking.

“Shoo.” He waved a gloved hand at her, but all it did was succeed in making her pad over to him and jump into his lap.

Kylo sighed - he lifted his arm to pet her, and she flicked her ears and gazed at him with her emerald green eyes, slowly blinking as if to say, “do continue.”

As the cat purred contentedly as he continued his ministrations, the force bond hummed to life and Rey appeared in front of him.

“I’m not in the mood right now, Ben -“ Rey’s voice cut off with a strangled gasp. “Kitty!”

“Er.”

“Is she yours?” Rey dropped to her knees in front of him, eyes wide in child-like glee, hand going immediately to scratch behind Millicent’s ears. The cat closed her eyes contentedly.

“… Yes.”

*************************************************

Oh Ben, you liar. *grin*

My apologies, it’s longer than five sentences, but I hope you like it!

title: seraf’s star wars fics
body:
you can justify it in the end - M rating, 97 chapters, 40k words. just a collection of like all/most of the canon compliant snippets i’ve written and posted on tumblr, compiled. 

the question of betrayal - T rating, 7 chapters, 3.5k words. cody/obi-wan. different possible endings to how cody and obi-wan’s story ends, most set in the original trilogy era. 

senator cody - M rating, 11 chapters, 6k words. collection of writing snippets specifically in the fix-it universe where clones get personhood and cody becomes their representative in the senate. 

named for endurance - T rating, 11 chapters, 3k words. collection of writing snippets in a daemon / golden compass type au, exploring the clones’ daemons, for the most part. 

only by surviving it, will you prevail - M rating, 10 chapters, 23k words. slight canon divergent au, exploring thire and darth vader in the imperial era, thinking about how initially thire was the one to find vader on mustafar. a lot of commentary on the republic vs. the empire. 

so it’s alright to kiss me anytime you feel like it - T rating, 1k > words. cody/obi-wan. first kiss crap, possible mutual pining, and fake/undercover dating, after the rako hardeen arc. 

cc-2224 (cody’s) files: general kenobi (obi-wan) - not rated, 1.5k words. cowritten with @depabillabaa​ and @stormphrax. cody/obi-wan. obi-wan loves him. he shouldn’t. cody loves obi-wan. he shouldn’t either. (does it matter?)

you made it this far - T rating, 1.5k words. dogma is living on borrowed time after rex negotiates for his place back in the 501st. 

official logbook: ct-5381 - M rating, 8 chapters, 6k words. tw: medical horror dogma’s journal after being sent back to kamino, recording the slow process of them putting him back together. 

dogmata - T rating, 2.5k words. a conversation that happens between rex and dogma on umbara, before dogma gets taken away. rex tries to be a good brother, but it starts to raise the question: is there room to be a good soldier and a good person both?

bad dog(ma) - M rating, 2k words. tw: self harm written for @letitrainathousandflames​ and their exile au. dogma is from the same batch as tup, and his chip begins to break down. 

the line of duty - E rated, 3k words. tw: dubcon set in the only by surviving it universe. just … it’s darth vader porn. it’s darth vader and thire porn. dead dove do not eat

the code of the republic - T rating, 1k > words. kiros has made the republic stance on slavery be noted; it is not tolerable, and they want to work to eliminate it within their borders. senator organa wonders how far that goes.

summary: The Skyhoppers Podcast: Episode CXVII - The Eyes Are the Windu to the Soul
title: The Skyhoppers Podcast: Episode CXVII - The Eyes Are the Windu to the Soul
excerpt: Time to put on your tinfoil hats and talk about how Mace Windu is Snoke! Not really. This week, we're talking about Mace Windu's grandson: Finn! This is a first for us, since we haven't seen the conclusion to his story, so naturally the show drifts into where he might end up in Episode IX! Do us a favor and check us out on Patreon! We give you a little each week, and we hope you feel that we deserve a little in return: https://patreon.com/theskyhopperspodcast Places to find us: Tumblr Twitter Ben's Twitter Ash's Twitter Facebook iTunes Stitcher Google Play YouTube Places to find Alexandra's writing: Tumblr FanFiction.net AO3 Make sure to leave us iTunes and Stitcher reviews if you enjoy the show! Find the other podcasts on the Star Wars Commonwealth on the website! If you've got something to say, any of the above will do! But if you've REALLY got something to say, email us at skyhopperspodcast@gmail.com.
